Since it'll be summer
and knowing how hot it'll be,

240
00:16:37,963 --> 00:16:40,966
we made this with an open shape.

241
00:16:41,033 --> 00:16:43,002
<i>For an unprecedented situation,</i>

242
00:16:43,068 --> 00:16:45,704
<i>they made strict preventative measures</i>

243
00:16:45,771 --> 00:16:49,641
<i>and planned to tour
from August to October.</i>

244
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:55,414
90% of them are waiting.

245
00:16:55,481 --> 00:16:59,518
I want to get to them as soon as possible

246
00:16:59,585 --> 00:17:03,255
and show them what we've created.

247
00:17:03,322 --> 00:17:05,691
That was at the top of my mind.

248
00:17:06,225 --> 00:17:10,996
<i>Once again, they begin
the journey to find their place.</i>

249
00:17:11,497 --> 00:17:13,799
Okay, this time it's for keeps.

250
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:14,700
Roll it!

251
00:17:17,503 --> 00:17:20,539
<i>In the midst of that,
they filmed a music video.</i>

252
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:25,044
<i>Their 18th single, "RUN."</i>

253
00:17:41,427 --> 00:17:46,065
<i>It was as though the four had
poured their determination into it.</i>

254
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:50,302
{\an8}THERE'S NO MEANING IN BEING RIGHT

255
00:17:50,369 --> 00:17:56,175
{\an8}JUST FIND YOUR OWN ANSWER

256
00:17:56,642 --> 00:18:00,379
{\an8}WON'T IT END? CAN'T IT END?

257
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:05,117
{\an8}WE STILL HAVEN'T MADE ANYTHING LASTING

258
00:18:06,952 --> 00:18:10,422
<i>"We still haven't made anything lasting."</i>

259
00:18:22,534 --> 00:18:26,638
<i>The four couldn't decide on
the placement for the song.</i>

260
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:35,481
When I think of it as a tour
during the pandemic,

261
00:18:35,547 --> 00:18:40,786
we could finish with "Yuki 100%"
and then reveal "RUN."

262
00:18:40,853 --> 00:18:45,691
I think that would
resonate the most with our audience.

263
00:18:46,191 --> 00:18:49,528
It would leave the biggest impression

264
00:18:50,095 --> 00:18:52,164
if it's after "Yuki 100%" for sure.

265
00:18:52,231 --> 00:18:54,566
The momentum of the group

266
00:18:54,633 --> 00:18:59,138
has to be prioritized, so I think "RUN"
towards the end would feel good.

267
00:18:59,204 --> 00:19:01,874
Run as hard as you can
and cut the goal tape.

268
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:07,045
I'm all for putting "RUN."

269
00:19:07,112 --> 00:19:10,883
But if we do, we need
some movement don't you think?

270
00:19:10,949 --> 00:19:13,986
So we'll do choreography
for the first chorus,

271
00:19:14,052 --> 00:19:17,322
but with the second chorus,
we could have movement.

272
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:20,626
<i>Then Nakajima brought up</i>

273
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:23,662
<i>the other meaning of this song.</i>

274
00:19:24,229 --> 00:19:25,197
You know,

275
00:19:25,998 --> 00:19:30,269
this song also includes
our feelings for So, right?

276
00:19:30,335 --> 00:19:32,404
"Nothing can start without you."

277
00:19:32,905 --> 00:19:34,873
It's a song with a message

278
00:19:34,940 --> 00:19:36,642
to connect to his hope.

279
00:19:36,708 --> 00:19:39,511
This could be that bridge-building song.

280
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:49,721
<i>This was about Matsushima,
their dear bandmate who is on hiatus.</i>

281
00:19:52,591 --> 00:19:54,059
<i>According to Sato...</i>

282
00:19:55,661 --> 00:19:57,462
Matsushima's having treatment,

283
00:19:58,030 --> 00:20:00,299
and information from outside,

284
00:20:00,999 --> 00:20:05,370
or the things we do
could mean more pressure for him.

285
00:20:05,437 --> 00:20:07,706
The four of us and Matsushima

286
00:20:08,807 --> 00:20:12,644
agreed to give each other some space.

287
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:17,683
That's what we've been doing.

288
00:20:18,784 --> 00:20:24,089
<i>And this was the t-shirt
they made for the tour.</i>

289
00:20:25,691 --> 00:20:29,261
<i>Each member is holding a can
colored with the member colors.</i>

290
00:20:29,328 --> 00:20:35,834
<i>In his left hand, Marius has
Matsushima's color, the green can.</i>

291
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:43,075
If we say, "It's Matsushima,"
people might take it the wrong way.

292
00:20:43,141 --> 00:20:45,510
They can take it however they like.

293
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:50,148
Matsushima's here,
and we're all taking a break together.

294
00:20:50,882 --> 00:20:53,318
We wanted to make that sort of atmosphere.

295
00:20:53,385 --> 00:20:55,954
That's how I see it, anyway.

296
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,157
AUGUST

297
00:20:59,224 --> 00:21:00,559
<i>And then...</i>

298
00:21:03,495 --> 00:21:05,030
<i>Sitting there was...</i>

299
00:21:06,298 --> 00:21:08,500
{\an8}Did you meet up often?

300
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:11,937
{\an8}We weren't like, meeting all the time.

301
00:21:12,004 --> 00:21:13,005
A few times?

302
00:21:13,071 --> 00:21:17,075
Yeah, a few times.
Visiting when we can, type of thing.

303
00:21:17,976 --> 00:21:20,078
Hey, let's go.

304
00:21:20,145 --> 00:21:22,981
Yay!

305
00:21:23,048 --> 00:21:23,882
Woo!

306
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:25,217
It's So!

307
00:21:25,284 --> 00:21:28,120
Yes. Sorry for being away for so long.

308
00:21:28,186 --> 00:21:30,222
I'm So Matsushima from Sexy Zone.

309
00:21:32,524 --> 00:21:37,763
When we sing it, the meaning
really is mainly about So.

310
00:21:37,829 --> 00:21:39,931
{\an8}<i>On the next</i> RIDE ON TIME<i>...</i>

311
00:21:39,998 --> 00:21:42,434
{\an8}Yay!

312
00:21:42,501 --> 00:21:43,669
{\an8}It's So!

313
00:21:43,735 --> 00:21:44,569
{\an8}Yes.

314
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:47,939
{\an8}<i>Finally, they were five once more.</i>

315
00:21:49,741 --> 00:21:53,979
{\an8}<i>Behind that were the unspoken feelings
for their bandmate.</i>

316
00:21:54,046 --> 00:21:56,281
{\an8}He might not come back.

317
00:21:56,348 --> 00:22:00,585
{\an8}If So is happy that way, then that's okay.

318
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:04,589
{\an8}I can't say, "Please, I want to perform
as five. Please come back."

319
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:09,428
{\an8}As long as he's healthy.
That's all that matters.

320
00:22:10,896 --> 00:22:14,966
{\an8}<i>There are places they can find
only as a five-man group.</i>

321
00:22:15,033 --> 00:22:16,935
